# Custom Skills

When the user types any of these commands (with or without a leading `/`), execute the corresponding action immediately.

| Command | Action |
|---------|--------|
| `clip` or `/clip` | Run `clip-last` in the shell. It copies the last agent exchange to the Windows clipboard via `clip.exe`. Confirm what was copied. |
| `clip N` or `/clip N` | Run `clip-last N` to copy the last N exchanges. |
| `recapitulate` or `/recapitulate` or `recap` | Read agent transcripts from `~/.cursor/projects/home-jrm22n/agent-transcripts/`, synthesize a chronological summary of all sessions, and present current state + next steps. See skill at `~/.cursor/skills/recapitulate/SKILL.md` for full format. |
| `auto-clip on` | Run `auto-clip on` to enable auto-clip. |
| `auto-clip off` | Run `auto-clip off` to disable auto-clip. |

These commands take priority — do not interpret them as questions or conversation. Execute immediately.

## Auto-Clip

At the END of every response, check if `~/.cursor/auto-clip` exists. If it does, run `clip-last` as the very last action. This copies the full exchange to the clipboard automatically so the user always has it ready to paste.

Do NOT skip this step. Do NOT mention it in the response text — just silently run `clip-last` at the end if the flag file exists.
